Here's what you need:

## XAML

```xml
<RefreshView IsRefreshing="{Binding IsRefreshing}"
             Command="{Binding RefreshCommand}">
    <CollectionView ItemsSource="{Binding Items}"
                    SelectionMode="Single"
                    SelectedItem="{Binding CurrentItem, Mode=TwoWay}"
                    SelectionChangedCommand="{Binding ItemSelectedCommand}">
        <CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
            <DataTemplate x:DataType="models:Item">
                <Grid Padding="12" ColumnDefinitions="48,*">
                    <Image Source="{Binding Icon}" WidthRequest="40" HeightRequest="40" />
                    <Label Grid.Column="1" Text="{Binding Name}" VerticalOptions="Center" />
                </Grid>
            </DataTemplate>
        </CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
        <CollectionView.EmptyView>
            <ContentView>
                <Label Text="No items found."
                       HorizontalOptions="Center" VerticalOptions="Center" />
            </ContentView>
        </CollectionView.EmptyView>
    </CollectionView>
</RefreshView>
```

## ViewModel

```csharp
public partial class ItemsViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    private readonly IApiService _api;
    private readonly INavigationService _nav;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private ObservableCollection<Item> items = new();

    [ObservableProperty]
    private Item? currentItem;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool isRefreshing;

    // Pull-to-refresh: reload from API, then set IsRefreshing = false
    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task RefreshAsync()
    {
        var data = await _api.GetItemsAsync();
        MainThread.BeginInvokeOnMainThread(() =>
        {
            Items.Clear();
            foreach (var item in data)
                Items.Add(item);
        });
        IsRefreshing = false;
    }

    // Selection: navigate to detail, then clear selection
    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task ItemSelectedAsync()
    {
        if (CurrentItem is null) return;
        await _nav.NavigateToDetailAsync(CurrentItem);
        CurrentItem = null; // reset so the same item can be re-selected
    }
}
```

## Key binding points

| XAML Property | ViewModel Property | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `RefreshView.IsRefreshing` | `IsRefreshing` (bool) | Set `false` when refresh completes |
| `RefreshView.Command` | `RefreshCommand` | Triggers API reload |
| `CollectionView.ItemsSource` | `Items` | Must be `ObservableCollection<T>` |
| `CollectionView.SelectedItem` | `CurrentItem` (TwoWay) | Null it after navigating so re-selection works |
| `SelectionChangedCommand` | `ItemSelectedCommand` | Fires on tap; handles navigation |

**Important notes:**
- Use `ObservableCollection<T>`, not `List<T>`, so adds/removes update the UI.
- Update the collection on the **UI thread** (`MainThread.BeginInvokeOnMainThread`).
- Set `x:DataType` on the `DataTemplate` for compiled bindings.
- Never use `ViewCell` — use a `Grid` or `StackLayout` as the template root.
- Reset `CurrentItem = null` after navigation so the user can tap the same item again.
